<!-- A preliminary version of this exercises was written by Weidai Sun after the 2024 Doenet workshop -->

<setup> 
  <selectFromSequence name="t" from="3" to="5" step="1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="s" from="2" to="4" step="1" exclude="$t"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="P" from="380" to="390" step="2"/>

  <function name="A">$P + 4*$s*$t + 2*$t*x + 2*$s*$P/x</function>
  <derivative name="AP">$A</derivative>

  <number name="crNum">sqrt($s*$P/$t)</number>
  <number name="absMax">$$A($crNum)</number>
  <number name="widthMax">$crNum + 2*$s</number>
  <number name="heightMax">$P/$crNum + 2*$t</number>
  <mathList name="dimsMax"> $widthMax $heightMax</mathList>
  <mathList name="dimsEntered"> $wEntered $hEntered</mathList>
</setup>  

<p> 
  The top and bottom margins of a poster are <m>$t</m> cm and the side margins are each <m>$s</m> cm. If the area of printed material on the poster is fixed at <m>$P</m> square centimeters, find the dimensions of the poster with the smallest area.
</p>
  <graph displayXAxis="false" displayYAxis="false" showNavigation="false" showBorder="false" aspectRatio="2" xmin="-10" xmax="10" ymin="-11" ymax="11">
    <rectangle name="r7" center="(0,0)" width="16" height="20" styleNumber="5" fixed/>
    <rectangle name="r8" center="(0,0)" width="12" height="10" styleNumber="5" fixed/>
    <rectangle name="r9" center="(-7,7.5)" width="2" height="5" styleNumber="5" fixed/>
    <rectangle name="r10" center="(-7,-7.5)" width="2" height="5" styleNumber="5" fixed/>
    <rectangle name="r11" center="(7,7.5)" width="2" height="5" styleNumber="5" fixed/>
    <rectangle name="r12" center="(7,-7.5)" width="2" height="5" styleNumber="5" fixed/>
    <label anchor="(0,0)" fixed><alert> printed material</alert></label>    
  </graph>

<p> 
  The absolute maximum total area of the poster is <m>A = </m><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute>$absMax</answer> square centimeters and this absolute maximum occurs when the dimensions of the poster are <mathInput name="wEntered"/> cm <m>\times</m> <mathInput name="hEntered"/> cm <answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute unorderedCompare><award><when>$dimsEntered=$dimsMax </when></award></answer>.
</p>  